America Movil Says Regulator Approved Bid to Buy Rest of Telmex

-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 
2011-10-10T13:14:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/america-movil-says-regulator-approved-bid-to-buy-rest-of-telmex.html
America Movil  SAB, the wireless
carrier controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , said it obtained
an approval from Mexico’s securities regulator to make an offer
to buy the Telefonos de Mexico SAB shares it doesn’t own.  The offer to buy the 40 percent of the phone company known
as Telmex will be valid from Oct. 11 to Nov. 11, America Movil
said in a statement sent to the stock exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carlos Manuel Rodriguez in Mexico City at 
 carlosmr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Elstrom at 
 pelstrom@bloomberg.net  